FBIS4-48388 "drafr096_c_94004" FBIS-AFR-94-096 Daily Report 17 May 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Plan Drafted To Send Peacekeeping Troops to Rwanda Plan Drafted To Send Peacekeeping Troops to Rwanda MB1705164094 Johannesburg Channel Africa Radio in English 1600 GMT 17 May 94 MB1705164094 Johannesburg Channel Africa Radio English BFN [Text] The South African Ministry of Foreign Affairs says South Africa has drawn up plans to send troops to Rwanda to join the UN peacekeeping force there, but political decisions still have to be taken. An official of the ministry said the plans had been submitted to South Africa's political leadership.
